        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5767",
        "content": "She said, It hath reached me, O auspicious King, that Ala al Din continued, \"So he packed me fifty loads of goods and gave me ten thousand dinars, wherewith I set out for Baghdad; but when I reached the Lion's Copse, the wild Arabs came out against me and took all my goods and monies.",
